Cases of coronavirus (COVID-19) have been confirmed in Barbados. The Barbados authorities have introduced a number of measures to limit the spread of the virus.
The Government of Barbados has announced that anyone arriving in Barbados with a travel history from Hubei Province (China), Iran, Italy and South Korea will be subject to a 14 day quarantine. Individuals who have visited other parts of China in the past 14 days will be screened and if necessary, also placed in quarantine.
The Barbados Ministry of Health and Wellness has a COVID-19 hotline staffed by public health officers 24 hours a day on +1 246 536 4500. The Government has announced that all public gatherings such as sporting and cultural events or any event that attracts crowds will be restricted to 100 persons. Visits by members of the public to all public and private geriatric institutions have been suspended until further notice.
Further information on coronavirus, including advice on preparing for foreign travel and helping reduce the spread of the virus, is available from Public Health England and on the TravelHealthPro website.
